# Extension / Plugin Development

## Structure

Extensions live under `extensions/*` as workspace packages in the pnpm monorepo.

## Dependency Rules

- Keep plugin-only deps in the extension's own `package.json`, NOT root `package.json`.
- Runtime deps must be in `dependencies` (install runs `npm install --omit=dev`).
- Avoid `workspace:*` in `dependencies` — it breaks npm install.
- Put `openclaw` in `devDependencies` or `peerDependencies` (runtime resolves via jiti alias).
- Any patched dependency (`pnpm.patchedDependencies`) must use exact versions.
- Patching dependencies requires explicit approval.

## Channel Extensions

When adding/modifying channel extensions:
- Consider ALL built-in + extension channels when refactoring shared logic (routing, allowlists, pairing, command gating, onboarding, docs).
- Update `.github/labeler.yml` and create matching GitHub labels.
- Update every UI surface and docs (macOS app, web UI, mobile, onboarding/overview docs).

## Plugin Distribution

- Preferred path: npm package distribution + local extension loading for dev.
- New skills should be published to ClawHub first, not added to core.
- The bar for adding optional plugins to core is intentionally high.
- Plugin docs: `docs/tools/plugin.md`.

## Local LLM & ComfyUI Notes

When developing extensions for local language models or ComfyUI integration:
- Follow the same extension structure under `extensions/`.
- Keep external service dependencies optional and well-documented.
- Consider offline/local-first operation patterns.
